    accion: "This triad articulates heat elimination and regulation of ascending Yang through the organism's elimination and descent pathways. The Large Intestine (Yangming) eliminates heat through the digestive pathways; the Bladder (Taiyang) regulates descending Yang along the back and directs energy downward; the Liver regulates bodily Qi and, when there is hepatic heat, contributes to ascending Yang that these two pathways must contain and eliminate. Er Jian (LI2) eliminates Yangming heat rapidly. Zhi Yin (BL67) acts at the distal end of the body's longest channel, moving energy from the feet toward the head and regulating Taiyang energy flow. Xing Jian (LV2) disperses Liver fire and regulates ascending Yang — the main cause of hypertension, headache, and irritability in these patients. Acts on the pattern of ascending Yang with Yangming heat: headache, irritability, inflammations, emotional tension. A dispersing triad, indicated in excess, especially useful in hypertension from ascending Liver Yang with Yangming heat.",
